  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It is possible that θρηνέω[a] should be classified only in Domain 52 Funerals and Burial, in view of the fact that θρηνέω[a] may in many contexts suggest a formal type of ritual expression.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>ὀδυρμός ({D:52.3}) apparently differs in meaning from θρηνέω[c] ({D:52.2}) in being less institutionalized and focusing somewhat more upon the wailing at funerals, while θρηνέω[b] denotes the singing of a dirge (see {D:33.115}). See also {D:33.116} and {D:25.141}. The meanings in Domain 52 differ in that they reflect ritualized wailing.</Content>
    </Note>
  </Notes>
